-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
# PLACEHOLDER — replace with your real cosign public key.
#
# Generate a keypair (no fetch-and-execute; cosign ships on mareOS / via `dnf`):
#     cosign generate-key-pair
#
# This produces:
#   cosign.pub  -> commit it here (overwrite this file)
#   cosign.key  -> DO NOT commit (it is .gitignored). Add its contents as the
#                  GitHub Actions repository secret named SIGNING_SECRET.
#
# The BlueBuild `signing` module + build.yml use the private key to sign the
# published image; this public key lets users verify it:
#     cosign verify --key cosign.pub ghcr.io/<your-user>/mareos
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
